value.0: Hardened by the hostile environment, trained extensively and outfitted with high quality equipment, the men and women of the Forrstakkr Guard are a more than capable fighting force in the harsh northern environment. Augmented by veterans from the Ostland conflict, this force is quite ready to protect and fight for the people of Forrstakkr.

With gear suited to the cold and frozen surroundings, these well trained and keen eyed rangers look as though they would be able to almost disappear into the wild when needed. Acting as the eyes and ears of Forrstakkr, as well as the first line of defense, they are all dedicated to protecting the people of Forrstakkr from whatever may threaten.
This magic bow has a bonus to attack. As well, it allows the wielder to add part of his strength modifier to the damage dealt.

A rugged, gruff looking man, Jorlief's appearance fits his role as Captain and supreme commander of the Forrstakkr Guard. He's an experienced fighter who is a master of his weapon - a bastard sword - and a Divine Champion of Helm. Jorlief's experience on the battlefield can be seen not only by the hardness of his eyes and the manner in which he carries himself, but also by the easily seen battle scar that runs across his right eye. The fact he is not blind in that eye is another testament to his combat prowess. He leads his men with a firm, disciplined efficiency.

Predatory blue eyes keep careful watch on the surroundings, including you. One could not easily mistake this wolf for a dog. However, unlike its brethren which stalk the wilds this one seems to have been somewhat domesticated. While the guards of Forrstakkr have found a way to domesticate the wild wolves, it seems unlikely they would take as kindly to outsiders.

"Tukson Devers of Cordor, Namer of Oghma. The extensive archive in this library was provided by his hard work and the people of Forrstakkr are forever grateful for this gift of knowledge he has given, even in this far corner of Toril."

Value.value: There's another ship leaving soon. Ya sure ya don't want to be on it?
There's another ship leaving soon, stunty. Ya sure ya don't want to be on it?
Go bash yer head on a rock!
Oi, dint yer parents feed you? Well, queenie, I ent EITHER!
*he gives you poisonous look, and speaks in a low growl* Get out of my town, spider vither.
*he does not talk, but merely opens and closes his mouth noiselessly, like a goldfish, before doubling over in peals of laughter*
Sod it, monkey.
*Looks around for somewhere to take cover* Shove a rock up it!
Why don't ya take yer namby pamby ways and... skip off!
Hop it, ya thievin' little midget!
*he gives you poisonous look, and speaks in a low growl* Get out of my town, spider vither.
Shove off or I git me flyswatter!
*sniffs the air* Bloomin' eck. Do you lot dissolve in water or something? Take a bleedin' bath, stinky!
*sniffs the air* Bloomin' eck. You lizards lay ROTTEN eggs, dogface?
Ya, ya, think yer all so perfect, don't ya? Well, why don't ya perfect getting the hells out of our town, cos we don't want yer here!
I've got my eye on ya, ya horned git.
Eh, where did we put those Banishment scrolls again?
Shove off, thicko. Do I have to spell it out for ya? We don't want ya here! Oh, sorry, I forgot, ya can't read, can ya?
Well I suppose yer not too bad. I s'ppose.
Well I suppose yer not too bad, fatty. *he begrudgingly admits*
Hmph. The boat out of here is THAT way.
Well, skinny, yer alright, I s'ppose.
Hmph. The boat out of here is THAT way.
Yer not too bad, are ya, me old herring?
Well, shorty longarms, I have to admit: Yer not so bad.
Hmph. The boat out of here is THAT way.
Well, stranger, yer alright, I suppose.
Well, shorty. I have to admit. Yer not so bad.
Hmph. The boat out of here is THAT way.
Yer not too bad, fer an insect.
Hmph. Well, yer might be useful, but ya still stink.
Hmph. Well, yer might be useful, but ya still stink.
Well I suppose yer not too bad *he begrudgingly admits*
I've still got my eye on ya, ya horned git.
So yer did alright. Great. Now stuff off!
Here's a present for ya, for saving the day. *He gets out a book, entitled "A is for Apple" *
